  "why": "The paper provides a clear, model-internal hypothesis for why failures occur (CNN sensitivity to \"continuous perturbations\" tied to convolutional kernel sign zones) and backs this with mathematical formulation (Equations 1–4) and a directed testing design. It therefore offers partial diagnostic insight by linking discovered failures to model internals. However, the paper does not present direct empirical tracing from individual failures back to measured internal properties (e.g., visualizing learned kernels, correlating specific kernel sign patterns or neuron activations with the found failures) nor does it link failures to dataset bias or corrupted training data. The evidence is therefore explanatory and supported by comparative results (e.g., effectiveness, label diversification, and inactivation-rate differences), but lacks the empirical root-cause analyses required for a \"High\" rating.",
